<p><b>Samantha Power</b> (born September 21, 1970, in <a href="/wiki/Republic_of_Ireland" title="Republic of Ireland">Ireland</a>) is an <a href="/wiki/Irish_American" title="Irish American">Irish American</a> journalist, writer, academic, and government official. She is currently affiliated with the <a href="/wiki/Carr_Center_for_Human_Rights_Policy" title="Carr Center for Human Rights Policy">Carr Center for Human Rights Policy</a> at <a href="/wiki/Harvard_University" title="Harvard University">Harvard University</a>'s <a href="/wiki/Kennedy_School_of_Government" title="Kennedy School of Government" class="mw-redirect">Kennedy School of Government</a>. Power has been a winner of the <a href="/wiki/Pulitzer_Prize" title="Pulitzer Prize">Pulitzer Prize</a> and was a senior adviser to U.S. <a href="/wiki/Democratic_Party_(United_States)" title="Democratic Party (United States)">Democratic Party</a> presidential candidate <a href="/wiki/Barack_Obama" title="Barack Obama">Barack Obama</a> until March 2008 when she resigned from the campaign under controversy. After rejoining the Obama State Department transition team in late November 2008, she has been named to a position on the <a href="/wiki/National_Security_Council" title="National Security Council">National Security Council</a>.</p>
